description:
Worktree provisioning currently does: rm .beads/; symlinkSync(parent, .beads, 'dir'); suppressBeadsWorktreeNoise(). The symlink is the structural source of the merge hazard caught in projects/infra PR #39 — a squash-merge of a branch carrying that symlink wipes the parent .beads/ on main.

Prototype on real xtrm-tools shared-server mode (2026-05-12) verified:

- Modern bd 1.0.3 writes core.hooksPath as an ABSOLUTE parent path at bd init time.
- Hooks fire from the parent location for all worktree git ops.
- bd hooks do NOT re-scaffold a worktree-local .beads/ when invoked from worktree cwd (audit: .beads/hooks/* are pure 'bd hooks run' delegators).
- bd ready / create / update / kv set / close all work from a worktree with NO local .beads/, via git common-dir resolution.
- A commit from such a worktree produces a clean diff against main: no .beads/* deletions, no 120000 symlink modes.

Fix (replace lines 252-258 of cli/src/utils/worktree-session.ts):

  try {
    rmSync(path.join(worktreePath, '.beads'), { recursive: true, force: true });
    const tracked = spawnSync('git', ['-C', worktreePath, 'ls-files', '--', '.beads'],
      { encoding: 'utf8', stdio: 'pipe' }).stdout.split(/\r?\n/).filter(Boolean);
    if (tracked.length > 0) {
      spawnSync('git', ['-C', worktreePath, 'update-index', '--skip-worktree', '--', ...tracked],
        { stdio: 'pipe' });
    }
  } catch { /* non-fatal */ }

Also: delete suppressBeadsWorktreeNoise() helper (the info/exclude write existed only to suppress the symlink as an untracked listing; with no symlink, it's pointless). Update the existing unit test cli/src/tests/worktree-session-beads-noise.test.ts to assert the new contract: after provisionWorktree, .beads/ does not exist in the worktree AND tracked .beads/* files are marked skip-worktree.

Acceptance:
- After bd worktree create + the new logic, ls worktree shows no .beads/, git status is clean, bd commands work from inside the worktree, and git diff main..HEAD --raw has zero .beads/* entries and zero 120000 modes.
- Defense-in-depth (xt end findBeadsSymlinkIntroductions pre-push guard) remains untouched.
- Existing test suite stays green (cli typecheck + tests).

Out of scope:
- Older bd installs with relative core.hooksPath (separate bead).
- Specialists side port (separate bead).
- gitignore audit (separate follow-up).

In diff.ts, the drift detection uses mtime comparison with a 2-second tolerance:

```typescript
if (systemMtime > repoMtime + 2000) {
    cat.drifted.push(item);
} else {
    cat.outdated.push(item);
}
```

This can misclassify:
- Files copied with preserved mtime → marked as outdated even if locally modified
- Network filesystem delays → false positives
- Clock skew between systems → unpredictable behavior

**Impact**: Users may lose local changes or see incorrect sync recommendations.

**Recommendation**: Use content hash comparison with a manifest for drift detection.

